=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides information that defines a MongoDB data provider.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AuthMechanism => Str

The authentication method for connecting to the data provider. Valid
values are DEFAULT, MONGODB_CR, or SCRAM_SHA_1.


=head2 AuthSource => Str

The MongoDB database name. This setting isn't used when C<AuthType> is
set to C<"no">.

The default is C<"admin">.


=head2 AuthType => Str

The authentication type for the database connection. Valid values are
PASSWORD or NO.


=head2 CertificateArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the certificate used for SSL
connection.


=head2 DatabaseName => Str

The database name on the MongoDB data provider.


=head2 Port => Int

The port value for the MongoDB data provider.


=head2 ServerName => Str

The name of the MongoDB server.


=head2 SslMode => Str

The SSL mode used to connect to the MongoDB data provider. The default
value is C<none>.



